main event: A ground radar operator detected a single fast-moving target with a speed of 1500 mph for about 5 minutes south of Tonopah, Nevada on September 24, 1961.
interesting points: The radar target was detected moving at a very high speed of 1500 mph.
The target was tracked for approximately 5 minutes by the ground radar.
The location of the sighting was south of Tonopah, Nevada.
The report notes that further details about the sighting are unknown.
The sighting was made by a military radar operator, indicating it was a credible observation.
